main event: A circular yellow-white light, size of a pea, was observed in Omaha, Nebraska for twenty-one minutes on 30 August 1956.
interesting points: The object exhibited erratic zigzag movements from the horizon., The sighting duration was precisely twenty-one minutes., The object was categorized as a circular shape., The report considers various conclusions including satellite, balloon, and aircraft., The documentation is part of Project 10073.
